# Drivebit Clients - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a Kotlin Multiplatform project for Drivebit mobile clients targeting Android, iOS, and Web platforms.

## Code Style & Conventions
- Use Kotlin coding conventions
- Follow Material Design guidelines for Android
- Follow iOS Human Interface Guidelines for iOS
- Use Compose Multiplatform for shared UI
- Prefer immutable data structures
- Use meaningful variable and function names

## File Structure
- `composeApp/src/commonMain/` - Shared code across all platforms
- `composeApp/src/androidMain/` - Android-specific code
- `composeApp/src/iosMain/` - iOS-specific code
- `composeApp/src/wasmJsMain/` - Web-specific code
- `iosApp/` - iOS app entry point

## Build Commands
- Android: `./gradlew :composeApp:assembleDebug`
- Web: `./gradlew :composeApp:wasmJsBrowserDevelopmentRun`
- iOS: Open `iosApp/` in Xcode

